    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "Verse 10 has to go back to David `[char_David_Rut_4]` himself, for Christ has no failing because of His \u201ciniquity.\u201d Observe, for the hundreth time, the problems involved in really \u201crightly dividing the word of truth.\u201d It is not such simplistic childhood business as that set up by Bullinger, Stam, and O\u2019Hair (modern Dry Cleaners are Moore, Watkins, Brock, et al.). These inadept followers of Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2014who are no more \u201cPauline\u201d in practice than Bullinger or Cornelius Stam\u2014think you can divide the books up with razor slashes between them. You can\u2019t even do that to chapters .\nVerse 11 goes directly on Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ. Kroll, at Liberty, misses all four clauses like he was shooting at doves with a .22 pistol. \u201cA reproach among all mine enemies\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled literally to the letter (Luke 11:45), even more so in Christ\u2019s case than David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s. \u201cBut especially among my neighbours\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled literally to the letter (Mark 6:3), even more so in Christ\u2019s sake than David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s. \u201cAnd a fear to mine acquaintance\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled literally to the letter (John `[char_John_Ref]` 12:42), even more so in Christ\u2019s case than David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s. \u201cThey that did see me without fled from me\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled literally to the letter (Matt. 26:56, 8:33). When many of His disciples saw that He was \u201cwithout\u201d the religious camp (John `[char_John_Ref]` 6:66), they forsook Him. How did the \u201clife-long educational program\u201d and \u201clife-long Bible study\u2019\u2019 in your home through \u201cBible-Institute courses\u201d miss four references that dealt with the life of your Saviour? Kroll, who spent most of his life in \u201cword studies\u201d trying to ascertain \u201cthe original intent of the author\u201d (see the work or preaching of any lamebrain like A. T. Robertson, Kenneth Wuest, Trench, Gary Hudson, Doug Kutilek, James Price, or Arthur Farstad), missed the \u201coriginal intent\u201d even when it was in the plainest, boldest, and most obvious form possible. Par for the course. There is no cure for apostasy. Slander, rumors, and false accusations are the common lot of those who \u201clive godly in Christ Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`\u201d (2 Tim. 3:12). Those who get indignant and upset by such treatment are those who are living ungodly in Christ Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`. David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s lot is the common lot of \u201cthe righteous\u201d (vs. 18).\n11. Verse 10 has to go back to David `[char_David_Rut_4]` himself, for Christ has no failing because of His \u201ciniquity.\u201d Observe, for the hundreth time, the problems involved in really \u201crightly dividing the word of truth.\u201d It is not such simplistic childhood business as that set up by Bullinger, Stam, and O\u2019Hair (modern Dry Cleaners are Moore, Watkins, Brock, et al.). These inadept followers of Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2014who are no more \u201cPauline\u201d in practice than Bullinger or Cornelius Stam\u2014think you can divide the books up with razor slashes between them. You can\u2019t even do that to chapters.\nVerse 11 goes directly on Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ. Kroll, at Liberty, misses all four clauses like he was shooting at doves with a .22 pistol. \u201cA reproach among all mine enemies\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled [v_Luk_11_45] literally to the letter (Luke 11:45), even more so in Christ\u2019s case than David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s. \u201cBut especially among my neighbours\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled [v_Mrk_6_3] literally to the letter (Mark 6:3), even more so in Christ\u2019s sake than David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s. \u201cAnd a fear to mine acquaintance\u201d (vs. 11) was fulfilled [v_Jhn_12_42] literally to the letter (John `[char_John_Ref]` 12:42), even more so in Christ\u2019s case than David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s. \u201cThey that did see me without fled from me\u201d (vs. 11) was [v_Mat_26_56] fulfilled literally to the letter (Matt. 26:56, 8:33). When many of His disciples saw that He was \u201cwithout\u201d the religious camp (John `[char_John_Ref]` 6:66), they forsook Him. How did the \u201clife-long educational program\u201d and \u201clife-long Bible study\u2019\u2019 in your home through \u201cBible-Institute courses\u201d miss four references that dealt with the life of your Saviour? Kroll, who spent most of his life in \u201cword studies\u201d trying to ascertain \u201cthe original intent of the author\u201d (see the work or preaching of any lamebrain like A. T. Robertson, Kenneth Wuest, Trench, Gary Hudson, Doug Kutilek, James Price, or Arthur Farstad), missed the \u201coriginal intent\u201d even when it was in the plainest, boldest, and most obvious form possible. Par for the course. There is no cure for apostasy. Slander, rumors, and false accusations are the common lot of [v_2Ti_3_12] those who \u201clive godly in Christ Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`\u201d (2 Tim. 3:12). Those who get indignant and upset by such treatment are those who are living ungodly in Christ Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`. David `[char_David_Rut_4]`\u2019s lot is the common lot of \u201cthe righteous\u201d (vs. 18).",
